# Sequential GitHub workflow (v0.3+)

Same rhythm as v0.1/v0.2. See `docs/V0_3_WORKFLOW.md`.

1. **Branch:** all v0.3 development on `dev`. Merge to `main` only when a milestone is complete (PR).
2. **One issue per agent session:** implement, test, commit, push — then stop. Never batch M15–M21 in one run.
3. **One commit per issue:** message `#071 - <title>` + body `Closes #91` (GitHub number, not plan id).
4. **No monolith:** never leave multi-issue uncommitted work on `dev`. If that happens, user resets per V0_3_WORKFLOW.md.
5. **GitHub is source of truth:** `gh issue list` before coding; scope = that issue only.
6. **Never bump release version** (#090) until #071–#089 are committed.
7. If the user says "implement the plan", ask which **single plan issue** (#071, #072, …) to do now.
